8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three principles\", \"from\": 4262, \"to\": 4278}, {\"ngram\": \"no expansion\", \"from\": 4280, \"to\": 4292}, {\"ngram\": \"the battlefield\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4311}, {\"ngram\": \"no escalation\", \"from\": 4313, \"to\": 4326}, {\"ngram\": \"fighting\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4338}, {\"ngram\": \"no provocation\", \"from\": 4344, \"to\": 4358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both nations stress the importance of preventing the use of weapons of mass destruction and promoting nuclear nonproliferation.\", \"from\": 4360, \"to\": 4487, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Both nations\", \"from\": 4360, \"to\": 4372}, {\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 4380, \"to\": 4394}, {\"ngram\": \"the use\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4416}, {\"ngram\": \"weapons\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4427}, {\"ngram\": \"mass destruction\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4447}, {\"ngram\": \"nuclear nonproliferation\", \"from\": 4462, \"to\": 4486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Clash of Value Statements Hinders Ending the Conflict At peace summits and in broader communications with the world, Ukraine speaks the language of values.\", \"from\": 4491, \"to\": 4649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4611, \"end\": 4618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Value Statements Hinders\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4526}, {\"ngram\": \"the Conflict\", \"from\": 4534, \"to\": 4546}, {\"ngram\": \"peace summits\", \"from\": 4550, \"to\": 4563}, {\"ngram\": \"broader communications\", \"from\": 4571, \"to\": 4593}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 4599, \"to\": 4608}, {\"ngram\": \"the language\", \"from\": 4625, \"to\": 4637}, {\"ngram\": \"values\", \"from\": 4641, \"to\": 4647}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It rightly condemns unprovoked aggression by authoritarian Russia against a country seeking self-determination based on a conscious democratic choice.\", \"from\": 4650, \"to\": 4800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4709, \"end\": 4715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"unprovoked aggression\", \"from\": 4670, \"to\": 4691}, {\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4733}, {\"ngram\": \"self-determination\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4760}, {\"ngram\": \"a conscious democratic choice\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Western politicians and intellectuals have alsoused the language of values, arguing that by supporting Ukraine, they are supporting the right to democratic self-determination in the face of authoritarian aggression.\", \"from\": 4801, \"to\": 5016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4904, \"end\": 4911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Western politicians\", \"from\": 4801, \"to\": 4820}, {\"ngram\": \"intellectuals\", \"from\": 4825, \"to\": 4838}, {\"ngram\": \"the language\", \"from\": 4853, \"to\": 4865}, {\"ngram\": \"values\", \"from\": 4869, \"to\": 4875}, {\"ngram\": \"the right\", \"from\": 4933, \"to\": 4942}, {\"ngram\": \"democratic self-determination\", \"from\": 4946, \"to\": 4975}, {\"ngram\": \"the face\", \"from\": 4979, \"to\": 4987}, {\"ngram\": \"authoritarian aggression\", \"from\": 4991, \"to\": 5015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kremlin is insisting on a \\\"morality\\\" of its own.\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5022, \"end\": 5029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9736705105624864, \"rank\": 0.02402096336881434, \"text\": \"Kremlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a \\\"morality\", \"from\": 5046, \"to\": 5057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It claims to be waging a \\\"liberation struggle\\\" against Ukrainian \\\"Nazism\\\" and the imposed U.S.-dominated world order that disqualifies Russia.\", \"from\": 5071, \"to\": 5213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5126, \"end\": 5135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999552801465, \"rank\": 4.463501037987736e-08, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a \\\"liberation struggle\", \"from\": 5094, \"to\": 5116}, {\"ngram\": \"the imposed U.S.-dominated world order\", \"from\": 5149, \"to\": 5187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nothing is wrong with moral statements as such, particularly when they are honest.\", \"from\": 5215, \"to\": 5297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nothing\", \"from\": 5215, \"to\": 5222}, {\"ngram\": \"moral statements\", \"from\": 5237, \"to\": 5253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But moral stance may be a problem at negotiations.\", \"from\": 5298, \"to\": 5348, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"moral stance\", \"from\": 5302, \"to\": 5314}, {\"ngram\": \"a problem\", \"from\": 5322, \"to\": 5331}, {\"ngram\": \"negotiations\", \"from\": 5335, \"to\": 5347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In hisbookAmerican Diplomacy,George Kennan argued that American politicians' tendency to frame every conflict in moral terms was not helpful in building a pragmatic foreign policy.\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5378, \"end\": 5391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_F._Kennan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.851339120802407e-64, \"text\": \"George Kennan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_F._Kennan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_F._Kennan\"}, {\"begin\": 5404, \"end\": 5412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.325705564411834e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hisbookAmerican Diplomacy\", \"from\": 5352, \"to\": 5377}, {\"ngram\": \"every conflict\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5458}, {\"ngram\": \"moral terms\", \"from\": 5462, \"to\": 5473}, {\"ngram\": \"a pragmatic foreign policy\", \"from\": 5502, \"to\": 5528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen Walt, professor of international affairs at Harvard, who reminds his readers about Kennan's view, writes that moral or value-based language can be useful for rallying citizens and winning support.\", \"from\": 5531, \"to\": 5735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5531, \"end\": 5543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Walt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Walt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Walt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Walt\"}, {\"begin\": 5583, \"end\": 5590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 0.999999999609372, \"rank\": 3.8955304975600866e-10, \"text\": \"Harvard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"professor\", \"from\": 5545, \"to\": 5554}, {\"ngram\": \"international affairs\", \"from\": 5558, \"to\": 5579}, {\"ngram\": \"his readers\", \"from\": 5604, \"to\": 5615}, {\"ngram\": \"Kennan's view\", \"from\": 5622, \"to\": 5635}, {\"ngram\": \"that moral or value-based language\", \"from\": 5644, \"to\": 5678}, {\"ngram\": \"citizens\", \"from\": 5706, \"to\": 5714}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 5727, \"to\": 5734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it makes it harder for U.S. officials to bargain effectively with potential adversaries, either because we refuse to have diplomatic relations with them, or because even a mutually beneficial deal with a supposedly 'evil' regime is seen as a cowardly failure to uphold key moral principles,\\\" Waltwrites.\", \"from\": 5736, \"to\": 6044, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"U.S. officials\", \"from\": 5764, \"to\": 5778}, {\"ngram\": \"potential adversaries\", \"from\": 5807, \"to\": 5828}, {\"ngram\": \"diplomatic relations\", \"from\": 5863, \"to\": 5883}, {\"ngram\": \"even a mutually beneficial deal\", \"from\": 5906, \"to\": 5937}, {\"ngram\": \"a supposedly 'evil' regime\", \"from\": 5943, \"to\": 5969}, {\"ngram\": \"a cowardly failure\", \"from\": 5981, \"to\": 5999}, {\"ngram\": \"key moral principles\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6030}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" Waltwrites\", \"from\": 6031, \"to\": 6043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Bargaining Might Succeed When the United States is not seen as an effective mediator, other powers are eager to try their hand.\", \"from\": 6048, \"to\": 6182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6089, \"end\": 6102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6341597144939926, \"rank\": 0.5768898230911534, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bargaining\", \"from\": 6052, \"to\": 6062}, {\"ngram\": \"an effective mediator\", \"from\": 6115, \"to\": 6136}, {\"ngram\": \"other powers\", \"from\": 6138, \"to\": 6150}, {\"ngram\": \"their hand\", \"from\": 6168, \"to\": 6178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politicians who are not inclined to value-based approaches to settlements and who do not demonstrate a willingness to take sides and join the West or Russia eventually enter the peacebuilding arena.\", \"from\": 6183, \"to\": 6381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6333, \"end\": 6339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Politicians\", \"from\": 6183, \"to\": 6194}, {\"ngram\": \"value-based approaches\", \"from\": 6219, \"to\": 6241}, {\"ngram\": \"settlements\", \"from\": 6245, \"to\": 6256}, {\"ngram\": \"a willingness\", \"from\": 6284, \"to\": 6297}, {\"ngram\": \"sides\", \"from\": 6306, \"to\": 6311}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 6321, \"to\": 6329}, {\"ngram\": \"the peacebuilding arena\", \"from\": 6357, \"to\": 6380}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A majority of countries tend to adopt positions of multi-alignment, of double-dealing between Western countries and the emerging or re-emerging powers of the South in the broad sense of the term, including Russia,\\\"saysJean-Joseph Boillot, associate research fellow at IRIS.\", \"from\": 6385, \"to\": 6659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6480, \"end\": 6487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999999999886313, \"rank\": 1.0398824817237468e-11, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"h